license (original MIT license is available on
http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license). The main amendment consist of
the annexation of provisions that prevent the work under license or any other
drived work from being used with war purposes, or purposes related to death
penalty:

Copyright (c) 2011-2012 Julián U. da Silva Gillig
http://minibloq.org

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of
this software and associated documentation files (henceforth the "Software"),
to deal in the Software without restriction, including without limitation the
rights to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or
sell copies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is
furnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:

1. The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in
   all copies or substantial portions of the Software.

2. Under no circumstances, shall the Software be used with war purposes of any
   kind.

3. Under no circumstances, shall the Software be used in warlike systems of any
   kind.

4. Adjunted to section 2, the Software use is limited strictly to civil use.

5. Under no circumstances, shall the Software be used in systems of any kind,
   whose purpose is to assist in cases related to death penalty.

